Officials had confirmed three people were killed in the blaze; another has now died in hospital. CAPE TOWN - A fourth person has died as a result of the devastating fire in Imizamo Yethu over the weekend. Officials had confirmed three people were killed in the blaze; another has now died in hospital. At the same time, Human Settlements Minister Lindiwe Sisulu has met met with community leaders to assess the situation.Sisulu and other government officials visited the Imizamo Yethu community to assess on-site damage and engage with displaced residents. The City of Cape Town s JP Smith said collaborative relief efforts will continue. We are doing two meals a day and there is a mountain of donated resources via NGOs. Thousands of residents are still being housed in the local community centre and other venues around Hout Bay.WATCH: After the fire... Hout Bay residents begin to rebuild(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)